  "instructions": [
    "Rinse lentils and set aside.",
    "Heat olive oil in a tagine or heavy pot over medium heat.",
    "Add chopped onion and minced garlic, sauté until translucent.",
    "Stir in diced carrots, tomatoes, and candied orange peel, cook for 3 minutes.",
    "Add lentils, raisins, cumin, coriander, paprika, and cinnamon, stir until coated.",
    "Pour in vegetable broth, bring to a gentle boil.",
    "Reduce heat, cover, and simmer for 25 minutes until lentils are tender.",
    "Stir in fresh mint leaves and rose water, season with salt and pepper.",
    "Let the tagine rest for 5 minutes, then fluff with a fork.",
    "Serve hot with couscous or crusty bread."
  ],
